\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b secundiramea}: Stems (3·5-)10-40(-55) cm, numerous, purple or reddish below, glabrous or sometimes hairy upwards. Leaves up to 4·5 × 1·7 cm, light green to glaucescent, glabrous; lobes usually oblong to obovate, obtuse. Peduncles up to 10 cm in fruit, pale green and shining. Capitula 17-22 mm in diameter; ligules 5-9 × 2·5-4 mm. Disc 6-9 mm in diameter, rather elongate in fruit. Achenes 1-1·5 mm.{\i  Throughout the range of the species.}
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b intermedia} (Guss.) R. Fernandes,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  70}: 13 (1975) ({\i A. intermedia} Guss.): Like subsp. ({\b a}) but stems 3-15(-25) cm, usually glabrous, deeper red; capitula up to 25 mm in diameter; disc up to 10 mm in diameter; receptacle hemispherical-conical; achenes c. 1·5 mm. •{\i  N.E. & E. coast of Sicilia and adjacent islets}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b urvilleana} (DC.) R. Fernandes, {\i loc. cit.} (1975) ({\i A. secundiramea} var.{\i  urvilleana }DC.): Much-branched from the base. Capitula smaller than in subspp. ({\b a}) and ({\b b}). Receptacle hemispherical-conical or nearly hemispherical, with obovate scales, wider than in subspp. ({\b a}) and ({\b b}). Achenes c. 1·5 mm. •{\i  Malta, ?Pantelleria, ?Lampedusa}.
