\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 37. A. muricata} (DC.) Guss.,{\i  Fl. Sic. Syn.}{\b  2}: 490 (1844) ({\i Lyonnetia muricata} DC.). Like {\b 36}({\b a}) but stems and branches not more than 25 cm; lower involucral bracts relatively longer, the inner with wider hyaline margin; ligules absent; achenes 1·5-2 × 1·25-1·5 mm, subprismatic, with very conspicuous and prominently tuberculate-verruculose ribs; the outer with an oblique or nearly horizontal, lobed or crenate, rather thick auricle up to 1 mm, becoming progressively shorter and only a denticulate margin on the inner achenes. 2n = 18. {\i Grassy hillsides. • W. Sicilia.} Si.
\par

