\pard\f0\fs28  {\b  A. bourgaei} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i Pugillus }56 (1852) appears to be known only from the original collection from S.W. Spain. It is characterized by the receptacle with scales throughout and the strongly tuberculate, turbinate achenes which are only 1 mm long.
